VALUES
  ('a3748b7d-264f-4766-a129-1adecf562afb','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',0.0,'EXCLUDED — PE-acquired November 2023.',0.0,'EXCLUDED — already sold to PE.',0.0,'EXCLUDED — already transacted.',0.0,'EXCLUDED.',0.0,'D_pass','D-pass / EXCLUDE: Silversand was acquired by Lincoln Road Global Management LLC in November 2023, merged with SLI Landscape and Zodega Landscaping into Houston PE platform. Founder Somir Paul → Senior Advisor. PE-affiliated, falls outside independent acquisition target profile.','EXCLUDE from target list — PE-owned platform.','high',0.95),
  ('0847f8b8-c9ae-4132-be31-358b30e048e1','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',28.0,'Kevin (current owner) ~47, only 26-yr tenure post-handoff. Well below succession-eligible age. Father Wayne handed off already.',78.0,'9 commercial testimonials (Northwest Bible, PCHP, U Dallas, ESD, American Honda) = institutional book. Kevin SMU EMBA = builder profile.',30.0,'Anti-coasting: Kevin actively investing post-EMBA, religious values branding common in long-lifecycle businesses but not a coasting tell here. 2 tells.',90.0,'Dallas DFW peak.',49.0,'C_watch','C-watch: mid-succession family business — Wayne handed off to Kevin (~47). Next exit window 3-7 years when Kevin reaches mid-50s. Strong institutional book.','Watch list — revisit in 3-7 years when Kevin (current owner) reaches mid-50s.','high',0.9),
  ('09d42550-7b19-4452-b955-607a8169a374','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',0.0,'EXCLUDED — PE platform since 2021.',0.0,'EXCLUDED.',0.0,'EXCLUDED.',0.0,'EXCLUDED.',0.0,'D_pass','D-pass / EXCLUDE: now part of LMC Landscape Partners (Trivest-backed PE platform formed 2021). Family Cox (Bill, Brad, Kyle) transitioned to PE model. Platform actively acquires others.','EXCLUDE from target list — PE platform.','high',0.95),
  ('0f19782a-8067-41eb-b36c-06759daf5fd3','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',0.0,'EXCLUDED — Monarch/Audax PE.',0.0,'EXCLUDED.',0.0,'EXCLUDED.',0.0,'EXCLUDED.',0.0,'D_pass','D-pass / EXCLUDE: part of Monarch Landscape Companies — PE rollup currently owned by Audax Private Equity (acquired from One Rock Capital April 2022).','EXCLUDE from target list — PE platform.','high',0.95),
  ('ee0bd80a-0606-498e-a324-f468ffe185b7','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',0.0,'EXCLUDED duplicate entry — same Texscape as spine #23 PE platform.',0.0,'EXCLUDED duplicate.',0.0,'EXCLUDED duplicate.',0.0,'EXCLUDED duplicate.',0.0,'D_pass','D-pass / EXCLUDE duplicate of spine #23 Texscape Services. PE-owned Monarch/Audax platform.','EXCLUDE — duplicate of PE-owned entity.','high',0.6),
  ('c17bcfea-8501-47d1-9189-24e50d34e9c1','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',25.0,'11-yr tenure, owner identity unknown. Hard gate: <15-yr threshold for ETA succession story.',55.0,'450+ commercial projects (hospitals/golf/hotels/HOAs) = solid commercial diversity, recurring vs one-off ratio unclear.',45.0,'4 tells: opaque ownership, 2024 stale footer, no published licenses, no online quote/booking. Marginal coasting.',82.0,'Katy/Houston metro commercial.',49.0,'C_watch','C-watch: younger company (11 yrs), strong commercial diversity but below 15-yr succession threshold. Owner identity opacity = DD obstacle.','Watch — verify owner identity + age via Comptroller. Strong commercial book if owner 60+.','low',0.45),
  ('f5404a2c-82dd-418e-8d63-6ab6964a57ea','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',25.0,'11-yr tenure, owner identity unknown. Below 15-yr threshold.',45.0,'Broad service mix (lawn/sprinkler/fence/fert/tree/hardscape/design), 50+ municipalities Sherman-Waxahachie. Owner-operator scale likely.',40.0,'3 tells: opaque ownership, no team count, no About Our Owner. Modern 2026 footer (current).',88.0,'Kennedale/Tarrant DFW.',47.0,'C_watch','C-watch: 11-yr DFW shop, broad reach, ownership opaque. Sprinkler license confirmed. Marginal candidate.','Watch — surface owner identity to confirm age.','low',0.5),
  ('0043975b-3c06-478b-b579-3b9f1c97e878','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',60.0,'Shawn Clayton age unverified but TX irrigator license LI1590 = very low number = decades-old license = likely 60+. 24-yr corp tenure with +3 modifier.',85.0,'300 employees + 120 trucks + 200 commercial machines + Dallas Cowboys partnership + multi-state (TX+NW AR). Highly sellable but well above SBA size.',85.0,'STRONG: footer copyright 2016 (10 YEARS stale!), phone-only intake, no quote system, no portal. Textbook owner-checked-out coasting at $30-50M scale = ripe for exit.',90.0,'Carrollton/Dallas peak DFW.',78.0,'A_acquire_self','PRIME A-tier: STRONGEST coasting signal in batch — 10-year-stale footer at $30-50M-revenue scale = owner Shawn Clayton fully checked out. Cowboys partnership = institutional flagship. Likely too large for solo SBA but A-tier for ETA fund / search fund. Deep dive pending: LinkedIn age verification + revenue size confirmation.','Acquire Shawn Clayton''s coasting institutional book. 10-year-stale website at $30-50M scale = enormous untapped digital + commercial growth lever. Cowboys + NW AR multi-state = scarcity asset.','medium',0.7),
  ('2c3ed8dd-9570-4428-88d3-3f438806d227','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',92.0,'Chris Easterling ~68, 45-yr founder tenure with max +5 modifier. Top of 68+ band.',75.0,'Commercial-heavy (multi-family/churches/banks/prof offices/municipalities/commercial centers) = sticky recurring contracts. 4-city presence (DFW + Tyler + McKinney + Longview) = real footprint. ~10+ specialist team.',78.0,'5 tells: footer no year shown, no licenses, no team photos, JotForm 3rd-party basic tool, ownership opacity beyond founder name. Modest scale but classic founder-coasting.',90.0,'Dallas/Tyler/McKinney/Longview DFW commercial corridor.',83.0,'A_acquire_self','PRIME A-tier: Chris Easterling 45-year founder tenure, age ~65-70, no visible succession, sticky commercial contracts (municipal/bank/church), modest team size = perfect SBA-financed ETA target. Deep dive pending: successor verification, exact crew/employee count, contract base details.','Acquire Chris Easterling''s 45-yr commercial book — municipal/bank/church contracts are sticky. 4-city operation = mini-rollup base. Modernize tech, retain founder 6-12 months for handoff.','medium',0.75),
  ('70d01daa-6b85-4811-8ac9-7a6f1e98a2b1','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',75.0,'Monty Theiss ~60-65, 40-yr entity tenure (2nd-gen, already through one handoff). Mid-upper band with +5 modifier.',72.0,'TCEQ license LI#6640 (very low = old/decades-deep), NW Houston corridor (Cypress/Katy/Woodlands/Tomball), design+install+lighting+maintenance + commercial.',70.0,'5 tells: entire leadership team in 50s-60s with grandchildren (aging team), Justin GM hire 2018 (operational delegation), Randy M 20+ yr staff = stable/aging workforce, install/design-heavy mix dilutes commercial maintenance recurring.',82.0,'NW Houston corridor (Cypress/Katy/Woodlands/Tomball) — strong commercial growth.',74.0,'B_forward','B-tier: Monty Theiss 2nd-gen owner with aging leadership team. Family-owned, no PE affiliation. Strong succession candidate but install-heavy mix dilutes pure commercial-maintenance recurring revenue thesis. Cap B due to medium confidence + install-heavy mix.','Forward to ETA buyers comfortable with design-build + maintenance mix. NW Houston corridor + 2nd-gen succession-ready + aging team = SBA-viable target.','medium',0.7),
  ('59fbec3e-b0f9-4a5d-a7d4-5bb03caee37f','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',68.0,'C.W. ~58-63, 33-yr tenure with +5 modifier. Top of 58-62 band.',35.0,'OUTDOOR LIVING / HARDSCAPE HEAVY — outdoor kitchens/fireplaces/pergolas/patio covers. Off-thesis project-based revenue model.',60.0,'4 tells: opaque full owner name, no license #, no employee count, lifestyle-business testimonial language (''known C.W. since kids'').',78.0,'Cypress/Houston metro.',56.0,'C_watch','C-watch: succession-eligible owner age + tenure but service mix is hardscape/outdoor-living project-based, not recurring-revenue commercial-maintenance thesis fit.','Watch — wrong vertical (outdoor living / hardscape) for ETA recurring-revenue thesis.','medium',0.6),
  ('517231a8-7fb0-4d85-9adc-c55892fa79d1','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',50.0,'19-yr tenure, owner age unverified. Mid-band placeholder pending owner identification.',78.0,'2,000+ properties maintained Austin metro + Highland Lakes = strong recurring book. Independence-confirmed.',50.0,'3 tells: opaque ownership, no team page, no employee count. Modern 2026 footer (current).',88.0,'Austin Travis Co. — top commercial growth.',64.0,'B_forward','B-tier: 2,000+ recurring contracts + Austin metro + 19-yr tenure = high-value book IF owner is succession-eligible. Cap B due to owner identity opacity (medium-low confidence).','Forward — verify owner identity + age before active outreach. 2,000+ properties in Austin = scarce recurring-revenue asset.','low',0.55),
  ('533c13de-bcad-456d-aaae-4bbc5ac160f7','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',78.0,'Founders Miguel + Patricia ~65-75, 29-yr tenure with +3 modifier. 2nd-gen handoff active.',78.0,'4-division operating model + 4 children in roles + customer portal (only in batch) = real scale + modern tech = highly sellable.',22.0,'Anti-coasting: customer portal investment, all 4 children actively managing divisions = active operator. 2 weak tells only.',88.0,'Rollingwood/Austin Travis Co. — peak market.',64.0,'B_forward','B-tier: family generational transition underway, founders prime succession candidates BUT next-gen continuity built in = more likely partial liquidity event or minority recap than clean ETA buyout. Cap B due to unusual deal structure.','Forward to ETA / PE buyers comfortable with minority recap or family-continuity-preserving deal. Founders Miguel + Patricia exit + 4 children continue under new capital partner.','medium',0.75),
  ('471246c8-2597-480c-8d1b-b8650e80db5e','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',30.0,'Owner ~45-55, 20-yr tenure. Mid-lower band, owner likely still growth-mode.',40.0,'Small operator, mix-trade. Limited sellability.',50.0,'4 tells: owner first name not disclosed, no employee count, no license numbers, small footprint.',85.0,'Fort Worth Tarrant DFW.',48.0,'C_watch','C-watch: 20-yr tenure at lower ETA edge, but owner likely still growth-mode and operator is opaque.','Watch — verify owner identity + age before outreach.','low',0.55),
  ('ee131878-6a9c-4b3c-9b6a-de7e12bed1bb','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',95.0,'David Felker ~67-72, 47-year trade tenure with max +5 modifier. Top of 68+ band.',72.0,'Husband-wife operator, Kathy Pinke office manager, long-tenured staff (10-15+ yr), residential+commercial mix. Modest scale.',82.0,'5 tells: STALE 2023 FOOTER (3 yrs stale = strong coasting), aging workforce (10-15+ yr tenure = stale), no online quote, no licenses published, no LMN/Aspire = textbook owner-coasting.',85.0,'Fort Worth Tarrant DFW commercial corridor.',84.0,'A_acquire_self','PRIME A-tier: David Felker 47-year trade tenure, husband-wife operator, stale 2023 footer, aging workforce, modest SBA-fit scale. Textbook ETA target. Deep dive pending: successor verification + crew count + contract base.','Acquire David Felker''s 47-year husband-wife operation. Stale 2023 footer + aging team + modest scale = perfect SBA-financed ETA buyout. Modernize tech, refresh team, scale Fort Worth book.','medium',0.75),
  ('d571fb02-331e-4093-b1ad-b26e027bab4c','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',35.0,'Owner identity AND tenure unverified. Hard gate: cannot verify pushes toward lower band.',82.0,'Pure HOA / commercial portfolio (office/warehouse/dealership/shopping/banks/churches/hospitals) = exceptional recurring book. Multi-county coverage (Tarrant/Denton/Wise/Parker/Johnson/Ellis).',60.0,'4 tells: opaque ownership, no employee count, no years stated, About page 404 (broken navigation). Online quote + pay = mild modernization.',88.0,'Fort Worth multi-county DFW.',62.0,'B_forward','B-tier: exceptional HOA/commercial book (banks/churches/hospitals = stickiest contracts) BUT owner identity + tenure unverified. Cap B due to low confidence + unverified owner age.','Forward — surface owner identity + tenure via Comptroller. If owner 60+, this is an A-tier prize for HOA/commercial recurring revenue.','low',0.5),
  ('ebde61e6-7a0c-4f50-b2a4-b828a73cfb2b','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',55.0,'Owner age + tenure unverified. Recent GM hire (Mike Sweeney Oct 2025) = pre-exit operational delegation signal.',70.0,'Commercial / HOA / MUD recurring book = sticky. Austin metro footprint.',65.0,'5 tells: year founded not disclosed, no license #, no employee count, no online quote, thin About page. GM hire = pre-exit grooming signal.',88.0,'Austin Travis — peak market.',68.0,'B_forward','B-tier: Bobby Montagne with strong commercial/HOA/MUD recurring book + recent GM hire = classic pre-exit grooming pattern. Cap B due to tenure unverified + medium confidence.','Forward — recent GM hire (Oct 2025) is the smoking gun for pre-exit grooming. Need TX SOS for tenure confirmation. HOA/MUD book = sticky.','medium',0.55),
  ('a401edd7-1640-4660-bbac-374a7975dd65','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',78.0,'Founders Jay + Yolanda ~65-75, 23-yr tenure. Top of 63-67 band — but operational succession to children already complete.',82.0,'140+ commercial properties managed + 3 children in C-suite + 100+ yrs combined exp. Highly sellable.',20.0,'Anti-coasting: 2nd-gen operationally complete, current 2026 footer, active modern operation. 0 tells.',88.0,'Austin/Cedar Park/Leander/Georgetown growth corridor.',60.0,'B_forward','B-tier: 2nd-gen handoff OPERATIONALLY COMPLETE — Tiffany Martin Peters is President, 2 siblings VPs. Family-business-continuity story, not ETA target. Minority recap or partial-liquidity event possible.','Forward to PE landscape rollups or minority capital partners. Family continues running, founders take liquidity. 140+ commercial properties + Austin = valuable bolt-on.','high',0.8),
  ('e69a8c4d-9146-409f-ab36-913684629c61','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',95.0,'Armando de la Peña ~70-75, 44-year founder tenure with max +5 modifier. Top of 68+ band.',65.0,'Commercial + residential mix, multiple trade-assn memberships (TX Turf Irrigation + Ecological Landscaping + ISA Arboriculture), modest team. Mid-range sellability.',92.0,'STRONG: footer 2017-2022 (up to 9 yrs stale!!), ''33 years'' claim outdated (actual 44), no license #, no employee count, no online quote, no successor visible. Textbook owner-coasting at high tenure.',75.0,'San Antonio Bexar — solid commercial market.',83.0,'A_acquire_self','PRIME A-tier: Armando de la Peña 44-year founder, age ~70-75, MASSIVELY stale website (footer 2017-2022 = up to 9 years stale, ''33 years'' claim itself outdated). No visible heir. Multiple trade associations = industry depth. Modest scale = SBA-financed deal fit. Deep dive pending: successor verification, crew/employee count, contract base.','Acquire Armando de la Peña''s 44-year SA commercial+residential book. 9-yr-stale website at this scale = enormous digital + ops modernization upside. Multi-trade-assn memberships = brand asset.','medium',0.7),
  ('d2936b00-37f9-44cb-8e93-bb98d38cbae1','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',20.0,'9-yr tenure, owner age unknown. Hard gate: <15 yrs threshold for ETA succession story.',45.0,'Family/minority/Black-owned, broad service mix (junk removal + seasonal decor = revenue diversification, not pure recurring).',35.0,'Anti-coasting: SA Current top-3 ranking + active growth posture. 2-3 weak tells.',75.0,'San Antonio Bexar.',39.0,'D_pass','D-pass: only 9 yrs tenure, owner likely growth-mode minority entrepreneur.','Pass — too young for ETA succession.','medium',0.6);
