  ('b42bbd8c-b4e7-4d9b-a7d7-b86ff3026b5c','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',30.0,'John Leifester ~45-55, 19-yr trade tenure. Mid-lower band, below succession-eligible age.',60.0,'Dual credentials (ISA Arborist TX-3484A + TCLP-0692), commercial install + ranch + tree work. Mid sellability.',45.0,'4 tells: entity founding year not disclosed, no online quote, no employee count, install/tree-heavy mix (less recurring than maintenance).',75.0,'San Antonio Bexar.',52.0,'C_watch','C-watch: solid credentials + personal brand but owner age ~45-55 = too young for prime succession. Unusual commercial+ranch niche.','Watch — strong credentials, niche play, but young owner.','medium',0.6),
  ('995f21de-b0e8-46d1-baf3-35d9a7b6f267','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',92.0,'Kevin Keane ~75, 47-yr tenure with max +5 modifier. Top of 68+ band — but operational succession to children already complete.',95.0,'200 employees + 10,000+ properties served + 47-yr brand. Highly sellable but well above SBA micro-acquisition (likely $20-40M revenue).',18.0,'Anti-coasting: online quote + online payment + modern tech, 2026 footer, active family operation. 0 tells.',88.0,'Wylie/Collin DFW commercial growth.',64.0,'B_forward','B-tier: TOO LARGE for SBA micro-acquisition + family operationally complete (Parker President, Hayden VP, Amy CFO). Forward to PE rollups or minority recap. File under ''family business not for sale'' but with PE platform upside.','Forward to PE landscape rollups. 10,000+ properties + 47-yr brand + Wylie/Collin DFW = scarcity asset for consolidators.','high',0.85),
  ('23974c2d-f2a4-4d3f-912e-145a48cdefb9','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',15.0,'Co-CEOs ~30-45, tenure unverified. Hard gate: cannot verify tenure pushes toward DROP.',35.0,'Small operator, broad service mix including seasonal Christmas lights. Sub-target size.',35.0,'4 tells: year not disclosed, no employee count, no licenses, small footprint.',88.0,'Frisco Collin DFW.',38.0,'D_pass','D-pass: young Co-CEO structure (millennial brothers) = operators in growth mode. Cannot verify tenure.','Pass — young owners, growth mode.','low',0.4),
  ('54af707d-ee51-4f41-a16b-300fa7a98a6a','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',55.0,'Jason Stubblefield ~54-61 (Navy vet), 22-yr tenure with +3 modifier. Mid-band 53-57.',62.0,'25+ employees + designers/masons/wood artisans, husband-wife operator, irrigation licensed since 2004. SBA-fit scale.',55.0,'3 tells: no specific license #, no online quote (phone+email only), no succession plan visible. Design-build heavy.',88.0,'Liberty Hill Williamson — Austin growth corridor.',63.0,'B_forward','B-tier: veteran-owned husband-wife operator at edge of succession window, 22-yr tenure, 25+ employees = SBA-fit. Design-build heavy dilutes recurring-revenue thesis. Cap B due to medium confidence + project-heavy mix.','Forward to ETA / search funds. Veteran-owned husband-wife exit + 25+ employee scale + Austin growth corridor = strong SBA target with design-build niche.','medium',0.75),
  ('e45dfd0d-5a2d-4739-a42c-e7155ac33244','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',65.0,'Nick Keller ~55-65 (30-yr trade tenure, 27 yrs at Keller), +5 modifier. Mid-upper band.',82.0,'200+ commercial accounts + irrigation/pesticide TX-licensed + TNLA + family-owned. Strong sellability for SBA-fit.',40.0,'Mixed: active DFW expansion claim = NOT classic coasting. 3 tells: no employee count, no 2nd-gen named, expansion mode reduces succession likelihood near-term.',88.0,'Georgetown Williamson — Austin corridor + DFW expansion = peak growth.',65.0,'B_forward','B-tier: 27-yr tenure + 200+ commercial accounts + active expansion = NOT classic coasting but mid-50s family-owned with no 2nd-gen named. Patient outreach worthwhile. Cap B due to active growth mode + medium confidence on age.','Forward — patient outreach. Owner Nick Keller mid-50s with no successor named = 5-7 year horizon for exit consideration.','medium',0.8),
  ('09aec707-939d-44fe-9983-24f71919e652','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',30.0,'Owner likely 40-55, 16-yr tenure. Mid-lower band.',55.0,'12 services + 5.0/156 reviews + 3D design previews + 5-year warranty = modern operator. Design-build heavy.',30.0,'Anti-coasting: 3D design previews = MODERN tech investment. 3 tells (mostly opacity): owner first name not disclosed, no employee count, no license #.',82.0,'The Woodlands/Montgomery NW Houston metro.',47.0,'C_watch','C-watch: 16-yr tenure barely past 15-yr threshold, modern operator with 3D design previews = active. Owner identity opaque.','Watch — verify owner identity. Design-build heavy mix off pure recurring-revenue thesis.','medium',0.55),
  ('8d324cd1-cede-45f0-ab3f-b8ce17c4fba0','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',78.0,'Doug ~60-70, 36-yr tenure with +5 modifier. Mid-upper of 63-67 band.',62.0,'Tree-care heavy (cross-vertical overlap), commercial maintenance one of multiple lines. Small team. BBB A+.',72.0,'5 tells: owner full name opaque, no license #, no employee count, no online quote, no 2nd-gen mentioned. Classic coasting profile.',82.0,'Katy/Sugar Land/Cypress/Richmond Houston NW metro.',73.0,'B_forward','B-tier: Doug 36-yr tenure ~65-70, classic small-shop coasting profile. Heavy tree-care mix = cross-vertical play. Cap B due to vertical-overlap with tree-care (not pure commercial landscape) + surname-only owner ID.','Forward to ETA / hybrid commercial+tree-care buyer. Surname needed for outreach. Small-shop family operator = SBA-fit.','medium',0.65),
  ('1335cae2-89b0-4049-abde-fc8002fbad86','642021e3-dffd-4d34-813d-15d18f2a88c1',55.0,'Eric DeFeo ~55-60, 25-yr formal entity tenure (35-yr trade), +5 modifier. Mid-upper 53-57 band.',55.0,'Outdoor-living + hardscape heavy, East Dallas/Rockwall corridor. Owner-operator art-degree background = lifestyle operator.',62.0,'5 tells: phone+email only (no online quote/tools), no licenses, no employee count, no team page, no footer copyright.',90.0,'Garland/East Dallas/Rockwall DFW commercial growth.',64.0,'B_forward','B-tier: Eric DeFeo art-degree lifestyle operator at edge of succession window. Hardscape/outdoor-living heavy = off pure recurring-revenue thesis. Phone-only intake = modest coasting tell.','Forward to ETA / search funds comfortable with hardscape+outdoor-living mix. East Dallas/Rockwall growth corridor.','medium',0.65);
